College_Name: School of Business, University of Alberta, Edmonton
College_Heading: School of Business, University of Alberta: Rankings, Courses, Fees 2024, Admission Criteria, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Alberta School of Business is a top MBA college in Canada with accreditations from AACSB. The university was established in 1916. The Alberta School of Business offers various undergraduate and graduate programs at Alberta School of Business in business, including accounting, finance, marketing, and management. The Alberta School of Business has about 39,000 plus undergraduate and postgraduate students. More than 6,500 students are called international. Up to half of all full-time students in the MBA program in Alberta are international students. According to the QS Global MBA Rankings 2024, the Alberta School of Business is one of the top universities in Canada, ranked at #121-130.

College_Name: Peter B. Gustavson School of Business, Victoria
College_Heading: Peter B. Gustavson School of Business: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Affiliated with the University of Victoria, Canada, Gustavson is one of the very few business schools around the world that is accredited by both AACSB and EQUIS accreditation. It also is the only North American business school represented on the Board of the European Foundation for Management Development. Programs at Peter B Gustavson Business School allows students to specialize in one of the three high demand areas of Entrepreneurship, International Business or Service Management. The Sardul S.Gill Graduate School of Business at the college offers postgraduate and doctorate courses.

College_Heading: Dundee Business School: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: The Dundee Business School is part of the University of Dundee's academic school system. The school collaborates with a number of other prestigious business schools throughout the world. Beginning in September and January, the business school provides undergraduate and postgraduate courses in business-related areas with a variety of specializations. Fall and winter are two intakes for submitting admission applications at the school.

It is the second-largest campus in the Texas Tech University System.

College_Heading: Millennia Atlantic University [MAU], USA
College_Summary: Millennia Atlantic University (MAU) is a private business school in Doral, Florida. Doral has been listed 22nd best places to live in Money Magazine. In proximity with Miami International Airport, Doral has become a hotspot for new residents, big businesses, and international buyers. It is accredited by the Accrediting Council for Independent Colleges and Schools and licensed by Florida Commission for Independent Education. The university offers 2 associate’s, 4 bachelor’s and 7 master’s degree programs. The university also partners with local as well as international universities to harbor professional networking and community assistance for students.

College_Name: Indiana University - Purdue University Fort Wayne, Fort Wayne
College_Heading: Indiana University - Purdue University [PFW] Fort Wayne, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: An over the top metropolitan setting and a traditional campus exposure together what makes Indiana University Purdue University Fort Wayne. The university sees a total undergraduate and graduate enrolment of 5,338 and 475 respectively. International students at the university approximately represent 3.3% of the total student population and come from more than 50 countries for higher education in US. Avila University: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Avila University is a catholic university providing liberal arts, professional, undergraduate, and graduate programs. However, international applicants must start the application process as soon as possible to receive timely admission decisions and complete the visa procedure.

College_Heading: University of Nebraska - Kearney, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: University of Nebraska - Kearney is a public institution that initially began as Nebraska State Normal School in 1905 and emerged into its present form in 1991. The university serves 6,200+ students and is currently home to 5,274 undergraduate students and 1,628 graduate students. More than 300 international students representing 50 countries add diversity to the student body. The university is located in the heart of Kearney and offers quality education with more than 170 majors and programs at the undergraduate, graduate, and pre-professional levels. Programs of the university are organized into 3 colleges of Arts and Science, Education, Business and Technology.

College_Heading: St. Andrews University, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Founded in 1960, St. Andrews University is a private university located in the city of Laurinburg, North Carolina. The St. Andrews Presbyterian College and Webber International University merged in 2011 to form the St. Andrews University, a branch of Webber International University. The university had a total enrollment of around 760 students including about 745 undergraduates and 15 graduates for higher studies in US. Amongst the total enrolled students, 84% were full-time students while remaining were enrolled part-time. Around 5% of the student body comprises international students coming from 26 different countries every year.

College_Heading: Lewis-Clark State College, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Lewis-Clark State College is a prestigious public undergraduate college which is ranked at #18 position in regional colleges west as per US News.
